e: 12(Noon) CST Until all events have been completed.<br><br>Each Event will have a point system.  Each time you win or participate in an event, you earn points.<br><br>Participation: 1 Point<br>Copper Medal: 3 points<br>Silver Medal: 5 points<br>Gold Medal: 7 points<br>Platinum Medal: This is the overall winner of all events<br><br>Event 1: Solo Sprint<br>Everyone will line up in front of the arena.  EVERYONE WILL TURN SOW OFF!  At the Gun, you will race around the outside of the arena.  Finishing back where you started.  This entire race will be done WITHOUT SoW and Selo's!  If you have it, don't cheat by casting it.<br><br>Event 2: Relay Race (2 to a Team)<br>This event will be much like the Solo race, but you will need a buddy.  For anyone that is left out, without a buddy.  I will race with you.  I will have my second account logged in and will oversee the finish line.<br><br>Event 3: Swimming<br>(Sorry Karn, you don't have to do this one if you don't want to)  we will all meet at the docks in Lake Rathe.  Again, I will have my secondary account logged in at the finish line.  What you will do, on GO, you will swim to the mountain straight out from the docks.  It's not hard to find.  You will have to get completely out of the water, Hail me and Swim back.<br><br>Event 4: Muffin Eating<br>This is as simple as it sounds.  Each person will be given a stack of muffins.  The first person to eat the entire stack wins.  This may sound easy, but wait until you are full and have to eat more and can't <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br><br>Event 5: Ale Drinking<br>We can't have an eating contest without something to wash it down.  So... we will follow the muffin eating with beer drinking.  You have to drink a full stack of Ale to complete contest.<br><br>^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^<br>***The last 2 events will depend on if we have visitors like we did at the last event.  If that happens, the last 2 events are canceled and will will just end the event with the drinking competition***<br><br>Event 6: Unarmed Combat<br>This event will be done in the Arena itself.  No one is allowed to cast any spells, or have any weapons in their hands.  You will have 10 seconds to do as much damage as you can.  I will keep track of the damage.  If you are scared that you may die during this event, I will cast Chloroplast on all people that fear death during this event.  I will also be available for Healing if that is not enough.  You are free to use what ever tactic you wish as long as it does not involve casting or weapons.  There is one final rule during this event.  NO MELEE will be allowed to Kick, Bash, Slam, Backstab, or anything other than main attack.  this would be an unfair advantage for those that are casters.  So casters... start working on your Hand-To-Hand skill.  Anyone that attacks early or does not stop when instructed will have points deducted from their score.<br><br>Event 7: Free For All (By Level)<br>Since I want everyone to participate in this event.  We will split up by level.  51-60, 41-50, 31-40, 21-30, 11-20, and 1-10.  Each group will have a winner that will be awarded points.  As a side note, since Lilbud is the only one that I know of that is actively in the top group.  We may have to test his kiting skills.  I'm thinking we take 2 or 3 people from the 41-50 group(depending on level) and see what they can do as a team, I will probably get in on this event if it happens.  YOU WILL BE ALLOWED TO CAST PETS AND BUFF YOURSELF BEFORE THE EVENT STARTS.  <br><br><br>All events will be logged for judging proof later for all desputes.<br><br>This entire day will be about HAVING FUN!!  And is the main goal of everything we do as Elites!  Start making plans now to attend this full-fun-filled day. <p>UNITED WE STAND!!To the world, you are one person, but to one perso